article.headline: Northern Iowa 69 South Dakota State 56
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa (AP) -- Eric Coleman had 16 points and seven rebounds and Northern Iowa had a 13-2 run to escape with a a 69-56 victory over South Dakota State. Grant Stout added 11 points and eight rebounds for Northern Iowa (4-1) and Kwadzo Ahelegbe had seven points -- including two three pointers -- in the winning effort. Matt Caldwell led South Dakota State (0-6) with 25 points. Though South Dakota State came into the game winless, it hung with the Panthers for much of the game, coming within a point midway through the second half. With 13:12 remaining, South Dakota State's Kai Williams hit a jumper to cut it to 38-37 in but in the next two minutes Northern Iowa used a 13-2 run to increase its lead to 51-39. South Dakota State never came within seven points after that.
